track_notes: I DO NOT RECOMMEND DOING THIS FULL TRACK! I originally planned to attempt to activate CO-094 followed by CO-092, Forest Hill.  However the terrain is extremely challenging with huge boulder fields and chest-high thorny bushes, especially after leaving North Star.  The hike up to North Star was 3.1 miles and is a reasonable bushwhack if you turn around and go back. I aborted my plan for Forest Hill when I realized it was impossible to climb up and get out before dark.  The hike down from North Star included 1,070 feet of elevation drop in 0.8 miles, it was dangerous and I will not attempt that again.  I ended up hiking out along the wash that runs between the two summits.  Beautiful but dangerous and remote.  I slipped several times and inured my ankle and rib.  Use extreme caution if you activate either of these peaks!
